HEADWORD: Holophote
<hw>Hol"o*phote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lamp with lenses
or reflectors to collect the rays of light and throw them in a given
direction; -- used in lighthouses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holophrastic</ent>⟦br⟧
